lender.name: Dino Go
lender.loan_because:
I believe that microfinancing in third world countries is one of the most effective methods to alleviate global poverty. This can be accomplished by giving incentives and opportunities to poor people the ability to have self-sustainable income. I highly applaud the work of one of Kiva's Field Partners, Alalay Sa Kaunlaran, Inc. (ASKI); besides microfinancing, ASKI's efforts also address educational and community development objectives.
I've traveled extensively in Africa and Southeast Asia, including China, and what I've found in almost all cases - regardless of ethnic background and culture - people make better decisions when they are well-informed. People also feel empowered to take positive actions when they have a stake in the conduct of their communities. Freedom, education and money or loans develop their greatest power when they are allowed to work together in unison. Any nation or society that paves the way where the poor are well-informed, enjoy their freedom, their rights respected, and are not living in fear, the money they have will always work wonders for them. Always.
I also enjoy and love to do something I feel good about myself.
